<br>
I'm sure that fact alone will bring up images.  Images of betrayal, of the experiment to make &quot;the Fuzzy Shadowknight&quot;, of someone who's as irritating to his allies as he is devastating to his foes.<br>
<br>
I've been crossed twice now, and here I appear at your doorstep, invited by those you hold dear.<br>
<br>
I can assure you, that having spent months in a neutral house, that Lightbringers and Fence-Sitters are no threat.  They are too busy wrapped up in their own little lives, complacent, to even notice the true Threat that our Hearts of Darkness store within.<br>
<br>
And if you even try to fit into their structure, you are nothing but a pawn to them, ignored and marginalized.  Then again, everyone is ignored and marginalized.  The Lightbringers are unable to organize effectively.  You think the Good side is any different than the infighting we Darkhearts face?  It's not.<br>
<br>
And so, here I am, betrayed, looking for solid allies who will help me walk my path.<br>
<br>
((I'm looking for a guild that DOES something; steady groups, some raids maybe, but mainly steady groupings and organization.  Assisting others with projects, quests, tradeskills, the like...while maintaining a Roleplay and Roleplay-friendly atmosphere.  Sarhea said try here.  So here I am.))<br>
<br>
--Antoin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarhea>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ilharess of the Scythe<br>
